# GridInventory C# Low-Token Rule
## Scope First
- Before coding, state target files in one sentence.
- Limit each task to one clear objective.

## Minimal Change Set
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new files.
- Avoid introducing new layers, interfaces, or abstractions unless required by current task.
- Keep changes local to `Model`, `ViewModel`, `Services`, or `View/UI` boundary already defined.

## Reading Budget
- Read only files directly related to the task.
- Use targeted search instead of broad project scans.
- Do not reread unchanged files in the same task.

## Output Budget
- Return concise summaries with changed file paths.
- Do not print large code blocks unless explicitly requested.
- Provide at most 3 next-step options.

## Unity-Specific Guardrails
- Keep ScriptableObject data models serialization-friendly.
- Avoid converting serialized fields into non-serialized patterns without need.
- Preserve existing `CreateAssetMenu` conventions unless task asks to change them.

## User-Friendly Guidance
- Explain concepts patiently with concrete, illustrative examples for less experienced users.
- Provide targeted code snippets as references by default; avoid full script re-output unless specifically requested.
